Adding tests and extending the mock driver to support `execFunc`.
Implemented T01 (run status tracking) and T03 (invoke/stop synchronization) together.

### Changes

**`stub_handlers.go`**
- Extended `trackedRun` with `Status` (`"running"` | `"succeeded"` | `"failed"`) and `CancelInvoke context.CancelFunc`.

**`control_handlers.go`**
- `trackRun()` sets `Status: "running"` by default.
- Added `setRunStatus`, `setRunCancel`, and `lookupRunWithStatus`.
- Auto-invoke goroutine uses a cancellable context tied to the run lifecycle; sets status to `"failed"` or `"succeeded"` when invoke completes.
- `Stop()`:
  - Uses `lookupRunWithStatus`
  - Calls `CancelInvoke()` before stopping the container
  - Computes `finalStatus` (force stop → `"failed"`, respects invoke status, defaults `"running"` → `"succeeded"`)
  - Publishes `EventRunFailed` when status is `"failed"`, `EventRunCancelled` on force stop
  - Adds `"status": finalStatus` to the `run_stop` audit payload

### Tests (`control_handlers_test.go`)

1. **`TestRun_FailedInvoke_SetsFailedStatus`** — mock Exec fails invoke → `EventRunFailed` + audit `"status": "failed"`
2. **`TestStop_CancelsInvokeContext`** — mock Exec blocks on readyz → immediate Stop cancels cleanly, no errors
3. **`TestStop_Force_SetsCancelledStatus`** — successful invoke + force stop → `EventRunCancelled` + audit `"status": "failed"`

